This paper deals with the management and maintenance of large-scale cellular networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper also uses machine learning models to predict future hot spots, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the regular and non-regular events that affect sector performance, which falls under the category of statistical learning (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
